name: Ecology
description: An introduction to the scientific study of ecology, emphasizing the structure and dynamics of populations, communities and ecosystems. Topics include population growth and regulation, competition, predation, biodiversity, succession, and nutrient cycling. Classic models and studies will be supplemented with both plant and animal examples. [24L, 18P]
prerequisites: (BIO152H5, BIO153H5)/ (ENV100Y5 for students in Environmental Programs)
